An Act providing for software licensing fairness.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 7D of the General Laws is hereby amended by adding the
2 following new section:-
3 Section 12. Fair software licensing
4 (a) A contract for the licensing of software applications, which are intended to be
5 installed by a governmental body and designed to run on generally available desktop or server
6 hardware, shall not limit such governmental body’s ability to install or run the software on the
7 hardware of the governmental body’s choosing.
8 (b) The secretary of technology services and security may promgulate regulations or
9 otherwise issue administrative directives to carry out the purposes of this section.
1 of 2

10 SECTION 2. Section 1 shall apply to any contract or addendum for the licensing of
11 software applications on or after the effective date of this act.
